When Ambrose was informed of the massacre of Thessalonica , his mind was filled with horror and anguish . 
He retired into the country to indulge his grief , and to avoid the presence of Theodosius . 
You have imitated David in his crime , imitate then his repentance , was the reply of the undaunted Ambrose . 
The rigorous conditions of peace and pardon were accepted and the public penance of the emperor Theodosius has been recorded as one of the most honorable events in the annals of the church . 
In this spiritual cure , Ambrose employed the various methods of mildness and severity . 
The cause of humanity , and that of persecution , have been asserted , by the same Ambrose , with equal energy , and with equal success . 
His epistle is a miserable rhapsody on a noble subject . 
Ambrose could act better than he could write . 
His compositions are destitute of taste , or genius without the spirit of Tertullian , the copious elegance of Lactantius the lively wit of Jerom , or the grave energy of Augustin . 
