But some remains of pride and prejudice still opposed the elevation of Arbogastes himself and the judicious Barbarian thought it more advisable to reign under the name of some dependent Roman . 
He bestowed the purple on the rhetorician Eugenius whom he had already raised from the place of his domestic secretary to the rank of master of the offices . 
