Ten thousand of those auxiliaries , and Bacurius , general of the Iberians , died bravely on the field of battle . 
But the victory was not purchased by their blood the Gauls maintained their advantage and the approach of night protected the disorderly flight , or retreat , of the troops of Theodosius . 
In the heat of the battle , a violent tempest , such as is often felt among the Alps , suddenly arose from the East . 
His victory was decisive and the deaths of his two rivals were distinguished only by the difference of their characters . 
Arbogastes , after the loss of a battle , in which he had discharged the duties of a soldier and a general , wandered several days among the mountains . 
Those provinces were involved in the guilt of rebellion while the inflexible courage of Ambrose alone had resisted the claims of successful usurpation . 
