Whoever will peruse the controversy of St . 
Jerom and Vigilantius , and St . 
Augustin's account of the miracles of St . 
Stephen , may speedily gain some idea of the spirit of the Fathers . 
I. The satisfactory experience , that the relics of saints were more valuable than gold or precious stones , stimulated the clergy to multiply the treasures of the church . 
Without much regard for truth or probability , they invented names for skeletons , and actions for names . 
The fame of the apostles , and of the holy men who had imitated their virtues , was darkened by religious fiction . 
A superstitious practice , which tended to increase the temptations of fraud , and credulity , insensibly extinguished the light of history , and of reason , in the Christian world . 
