At Minorca , the relics of St . 
observes , like a philosopher , the natural flux and reflux of polytheism and theism . 
As the objects of religion were gradually reduced to the standard of the imagination , the rites and ceremonies were introduced that seemed most powerfully to affect the senses of the vulgar . 
The Christians frequented the tombs of the martyrs , in the hope of obtaining , from their powerful intercession , every sort of spiritual , but more especially of temporal , blessings . 
They implored the preservation of their health , or the cure of their infirmities the fruitfulness of their barren wives , or the safety and happiness of their children . 
The religion of Constantine achieved , in less than a century , the final conquest of the Roman empire but the victors themselves were insensibly subdued by the arts of their vanquished rivals . 
