The fears of Honorius were not without foundation , nor were his precautions without effect . 
The youth of Toulun , the greatest of his descendants , was exercised by those misfortunes which are the school of heroes . 
He bravely struggled with adversity , broke the imperious yoke of the Topa , and became the legislator of his nation , and the conqueror of Tartary . 
His tents , which he removed in the winter season to a more southern latitude , were pitched , during the summer , on the fruitful banks of the Selinga . 
His conquests stretched from Corea far beyond the River Irtish . 
