Yet if they expected to derive any assistance from the tribes of Germany , who inhabited the banks of the Rhine , their hopes were disappointed . 
The Alemanni preserved a state of inactive neutrality and the Franks distinguished their zeal and courage in the defence of the of the empire . 
Marcomir , one of their kings , was publicly convicted , before the tribunal of the Roman magistrate , of violating the faith of treaties . 
They paid the penalty of their rashness and twenty thousand Vandals , with their king Godigisclus , were slain in the field of battle . 
