But those restless Barbarians could not neglect the fair opportunity of the Gothic war , when the walls and stations of the province were stripped of the Roman troops . 
Marcus was the first whom they placed on the throne , as the lawful emperor of Britain and of the West . 
Gratian was the next whom they adorned with the diadem and the purple and , at the end of four months , Gratian experienced the fate of his predecessor . 
The memory of the great Constantine , whom the British legions had given to the church and to the empire , suggested the singular motive of their third choice . 
Yet the authority of Constantine was less precarious , and his government was more successful , than the transient reigns of Marcus and of Gratian . 
The danger of leaving his inactive troops in those camps , which had been twice polluted with blood and sedition , urged him to attempt the reduction of the Western provinces . 
They obeyed the summons without reluctance . 
Elated , however , with this imaginary triumph , the vain deliverer of Gaul advanced into the provinces of the South , to encounter a more pressing and personal danger . 
Sarus the Goth was ordered to lay the head of the rebel at the feet of the emperor Honorius and the forces of Britain and Italy were unworthily consumed in this domestic quarrel . 
The place was ineffectually attacked seven days and the Imperial army supported , in a precipitate retreat , the ignominy of purchasing a secure passage from the freebooters and outlaws of the Alps . 
