After the praises of Stilicho became offensive and criminal , Claudian was exposed to the enmity of a powerful and unforgiving courtier , whom he had provoked by the insolence of wit . 
If we fairly balance his merits and his defects , we shall acknowledge that Claudian does not either satisfy , or silence , our reason . 
It would not be easy to produce a passage that deserves the epithet of sublime or pathetic to select a verse that melts the heart or enlarges the imagination . 
For the service of his patron , he published occasional panegyrics and invectives and the design of these slavish compositions encouraged his propensity to exceed the limits of truth and nature . 
These imperfections , however , are compensated in some degree by the poetical virtues of Claudian . 
To these commendations , independent of any accidents of time and place , we must add the peculiar merit which Claudian derived from the unfavorable circumstances of his birth . 
all the parts of animated nature contributed their various gifts and the gods themselves enriched their favorite . 
