Note M. Beugnot has pointed out one remarkable characteristic of Claudian's poetry , and of the times his extraordinary religious indifference . 
No one would know the existence of Christianity at that period of the world , by reading the works of Claudian . 
Under the child , and Honorius never became more than a child , Christianity continued to inflict wounds more and more deadly on expiring Paganism . 
Are the gods of Olympus agitated with apprehension at the birth of this new enemy ? They are introduced as rejoicing at his appearance , and promising long years of glory . 
The whole prophetic choir of Paganism , all the oracles throughout the world , are summoned to predict the felicity of his reign . 
His birth is compared to that of Apollo , but the narrow limits of an island must not confine the new deity . 
Non littora nostro Sufficerent angusta Deo . 
