At the distance of fourteen centuries , we may be satisfied with relating the military exploits of the conquerors of Rome , without presuming to investigate the motives of their political conduct . 
The king of the Goths repeatedly declared , that it was his desire to be considered as the friend of peace , and of the Romans . 
But the hopes of peace were disappointed by the weak obstinacy , or interested views , of the minister Olympius . 
The bishop , by remaining at Ravenna , escaped the impending calamities of the city . 
But the court and councils of Honorius still remained a scene of weakness and distraction , of corruption and anarchy . 
Instigated by the praefect Jovius , the guards rose in furious mutiny , and demanded the heads of two generals , and of the two principal eunuchs . 
This rash engagement opposed an insuperable bar to all future negotiation . 
