The usurpation of Constantine , who received the purple from the legions of Britain , had been successful , and seemed to be secure . 
The name of Honorius , the proclamation of a lawful emperor , astonished the contending parties of the rebels . 
In the middle of the night , a great body of his perfidious soldiers surrounded and attacked his house , which he had strongly barricaded . 
In this fatal extremity , he complied with the request of his Barbarian friend , and cut off his head . 
The unprotected Maximus , whom he had invested with the purple , was indebted for his life to the contempt that was entertained of his power and abilities . 
