This mischief was peculiarly felt in the provinces of Spain and Gaul , where the principles of order and obedience had been extinguished by war and rebellion . 
Every circumstance is dark and extraordinary in the short history of the reign of Jovinus . 
Adolphus connected himself with the usurper of Gaul and imposed on Attalus the ignominious task of negotiating the treaty , which ratified his own disgrace . 
He attacked Sarus at an unguarded moment , when he was accompanied only by eighteen or twenty of his valiant followers . 
The death of Sarus dissolved the loose alliance which Adolphus still maintained with the usurpers of Gaul . 
