Whilst Italy was ravaged by the Goths , and a succession of feeble tyrants oppressed the provinces beyond the Alps , the British island separated itself from the body of the Roman empire . 
The regular forces , which guarded that remote province , had been gradually withdrawn and Britain was abandoned without defence to the Saxon pirates , and the savages of Ireland and Caledonia . 
The Britons , reduced to this extremity , no longer relied on the tardy and doubtful aid of a declining monarchy . 
They assembled in arms , repelled the invaders , and rejoiced in the important discovery of their own strength . 
resolved to imitate the example of the neighboring island . 
