The usual methods of extortion were practised and improved and Claudian has sketched a lively and original picture of the public auction of the state . 
In the antechamber of Eutropius , a large tablet is exposed to public view , which marks the respective prices of the provinces . 
The different value of Pontus , of Galatia , of Lydia , is accurately distinguished . 
Lycia may be obtained for so many thousand pieces of gold but the opulence of Phrygia will require a more considerable sum . 
