Cicero might claim some merit , if his voluntary banishment preserved the peace of the republic but the submission of Chrysostom was the indispensable duty of a Christian and a subject . 
The mind of the illustrious exile was still independent but his captive body was exposed to the revenge of the oppressors , who continued to abuse the name and authority of Arcadius . 
The succeeding generation acknowledged his innocence and merit . 
At the pious solicitation of the clergy and people of Constantinople , his relics , thirty years after his death , were transported from their obscure sepulchre to the royal city . 
in the language of an orator and a politician . 
