The rapid progress of the Vandals soon acquired a more effectual opposition and the master general Castinus marched against them with a numerous army of Romans and Goths . 
The king of the Vandals is described to have been of a middle stature , with a lameness in one leg , which he had contracted by an accidental fall from his horse . 
His slow and cautious speech seldom declared the deep purposes of his soul he disdained to imitate the luxury of the vanquished but he indulged the sterner passions of anger and revenge . 
Almost in the moment of his departure he was informed that Hermanric , king of the Suevi , had presumed to ravage the Spanish territories , which he was resolved to abandon . 
See the Chronicles of Prosper and Idatius . 
