The Vandals , where they found resistance , seldom gave quarter and the deaths of their valiant countrymen were expiated by the ruin of the cities under whose walls they had fallen . 
Careless of the distinctions of age , or sex , or rank , they employed every species of indignity and torture , to force from the captives a discovery of their hidden wealth . 
The original complaints of the desolation of Africa are contained . 
