The two kings of the Gepidae and the Ostrogoths are profound politicians and sentimental lovers , and the whole piece exhibits the defects without the genius , of the poet . 
In the reign of his father Arcadius , a band of adventurous Huns had ravaged the provinces of the East from whence they brought away rich spoils and innumerable captives . 
Egypt trembled at their approach and the monks and pilgrims of the Holy Land prepared to escaped their fury by a speedy embarkation . 
The memory of this invasion was still recent in the minds of the Orientals . 
They related , during their residence at Rome , the circumstances of an expedition , which they had lately made into the East . 
They encountered the Persian army in the plains of Media and the air , according to their own expression , was darkened by a cloud of arrows . 
But the Huns were obliged to retire before the numbers of the enemy . 
