The Franks , whose monarchy was still confined to the neighborhood of the Lower Rhine , had wisely established the right of hereditary succession in the noble family of the Merovingians . 
These princes were elevated on a buckler , the symbol of military command and the royal fashion of long hair was the ensign of their birth and dignity . 
The death of Clodion , after a reign of twenty years , exposed his kingdom to the discord and ambition of his two sons . 
