One of the last acts of jurisdiction , which the Roman senate exercised over their subjects of Gaul , was the trial and condemnation of Arvandus , the Praetorian praefect . 
The second praefecture , which he obtained within the term of five years , abolished the merit and popularity of his preceding administration . 
He was eagerly pursued by his accusers , the four deputies of Gaul , who were all distinguished by their birth , their dignities , or their eloquence . 
But their intentions were discovered by the zeal of Sidonius . 
His complaints were soon removed . 
An early day was fixed for his trial and Arvandus appeared , with his accusers , before a numerous assembly of the Roman senate . 
The obstinacy of Arvandus was founded on the strange supposition , that a subject could not be convicted of treason , unless he had actually conspired to assume the purple . 
By their decree , he was degraded from the rank of a praefect to the obscure condition of a plebeian , and ignominiously dragged by servile hands to the public prison . 
This letter does honor to his heart , as well as to his understanding . 
