has observed the scandalous valor of the Cappadocian monks , which was exemplified in the banishment of Chrysostom . 
The father of the Benedictines expressly disclaims all idea of choice of merit and soberly exhorts his disciples to adopt the coarse and convenient dress of the countries which they may inhabit . 
They allowed themselves the use of linen in Egypt , where it was a cheap and domestic manufacture but in the West they rejected such an expensive article of foreign luxury . 
Thirty or forty brethren composed a family of separate discipline and diet and the great monasteries of Egypt consisted of thirty or forty families . 
