I am impatient to pursue the final ruin of that kingdom , which was accomplished under the reign of Sigismond , the son of Gundobald . 
He soon discovered his error , and bewailed the irreparable loss . 
The reproaches of a guilty conscience were alleviated , however , by his liberal donations to the monastery of Agaunum , or St . 
Maurice , in Vallais which he himself had founded in honor of the imaginary martyrs of the Thebaean legion . 
His prayer was heard the avengers were at hand and the provinces of Burgundy were overwhelmed by an army of victorious Franks . 
A martyr ! how strangely has that word been distorted from its original sense of a common witness . 
Sigismond was remarkable for the cure of fevers Before the end of the fifth century , the church of St . 
Maurice , and his Thebaean legion , had rendered Agaunum a place of devout pilgrimage . 
A promiscuous community of both sexes had introduced some deeds of darkness , which were abolished by the regular monastery of Sigismond . 
