A devouring host of one hundred and twenty thousand Germans had formerly passed the Rhine under the command of Ariovistus . 
At the distance of five hundred years , the Visigoths and Burgundians , who revenged the defeat of Ariovistus , usurped the same unequal proportion of two thirds of the subject lands . 
In these districts , each Barbarian was connected by the ties of hospitality with some Roman provincial . 
The memorable vase of Soissons is a monument and a pledge of the regular distribution of the Gallic spoils . 
observes , they were not a conquering people , who had emigrated with their families , like the Goths or Burgundians . 
The women , the children , the old , had not followed Clovis they remained in their ancient possessions on the Waal and the Rhine . 
The adventurers alone had formed the invading force , and they always considered themselves as an army , not as a colony . 
Hence their laws retained no traces of the partition of the Roman properties . 
